#AZBudget

These are commonsense solutions that guard the very important Second Amendment rights of law abiding Americans, while closing loopholes, protecting public safety and cracking-down on illegal activity.

Responsible gun ownership includes preventing access to minors. Our plan will increase the penalty to include prison time for any parent or guardian of a minor found guilty of illegally possessing a firearm.
Restoring gun rights to individuals with a violent criminal history needs to be scrutinized – not rubber-stamped. We need better policy to make sure this happens in our legal system.

For example: Background checks are only as effective as the data used to conduct the check. Arizona’s Computerized Criminal History Database is just 63.6% complete. Data can take up to 40 days to be entered by authorities. Let's require cases to be entered IMMEDIATELY.

In addition to students, parents and educators, my meetings on school safety have also included law enforcement professionals and prosecutors – of both parties. It’s clear: There are gaps in our system and in our laws. https://t.co/Sk3SHa4Amg
Thank you to all the Arizonans who brought your ideas to the table. You have greatly shaped Arizona's plan by offering meaningful solutions. https://t.co/JdXNgjyBZJ

Let’s learn from tragedies in other states. We need a centralized tip line to report – and actually investigate – concerns of school safety so they don’t fall through the cracks. AZ also needs more funding & enhanced training for school resource officers. https://t.co/4xe2rhzgNh

In the overwhelming majority of the deadliest mass shootings in the last 20 years, the shooter exhibited obvious signs of being a threat. Why not have laws and a process to restrict these individuals from possessing or obtaining guns? https://t.co/0DMu7BAVhJ

We are building an aggressive plan that address all these issues around school safety. Arizona can lead the nation in tackling this – and in a way that is non-partisan. We’ve done this on other issues, and we can do it again.

MORE:
✅ Respecting the #2A rights of law-abiding Americans, while enforcing our laws on the books
✅ Increased school resource officer and law enforcement presence at schools
✅ Closing loopholes
✅ Enhanced background checks

Some of the priorities I’ve heard:
✅Increased mental and behavioral health resources at schools
✅Restricted access to weapons for individuals who pose a danger to themselves or others
✅Cracking-down on people illegally possessing weapons
